SUMMARY: New Exhibits at the Brown County Art Guild!
DESCRIPTION:New Exhibits at the Brown County Art Guild!\n\nNow – March 14
 \, 2026\n\nGuild Artist Exhibition and Sale\n\nA new exhibition showcasin
 g works from our award-winning artist members who demonstrate a life-long
  devotion to their craft. On view will be a diverse collection of fine ar
 t\, with a focus on fresh perspectives and techniques. \n\nNow – March 14
 \, 2026\n\nFlowers in Winter\n\nSpecial Exhibition & Sale\n\nThis exhibit
 ion invites you to discover a world of silent resistance and vivid life. 
 Our artists capture the resilience of flowers against the cold...transfor
 ming a season of dormancy into a time of quiet persistence\, fragility\, 
 and beauty.\n\nNow – March 14\, 2026\n\nSMALL WONDERS\n\nPetite Artwork f
 or Sale\n\nInvesting in original art has never been more accessible. Stop
  into the Guild this holiday season to find the perfect tiny piece that b
 rings a little bit of joy to your friends\, family or yourself. Tiny canv
 as\, big emotion\, which little gem will speak to you?\n\nExtended to Jan
 uary 18\, 2026\n\nPainting Partners\n\nHistoric Collection Exhibition\n\n
 Marie Goth and V.J. Cariani\, along with Genevieve Goth Graf and Carl Gra
 f\, were immeasurably connected as they journeyed through life. All four 
 encouraged one another in their painting pursuits\, particularly en plein
  air. Each couple was aligned in their commitment to the growing arts mov
 ement in Brown County\, and their individual successes were undoubtedly a
 ttributed to the flourishing art colony as a whole.\n\n******************
 ******************************************************************\n\nBro
 wn County Art Guild – A not for profit organization located in the heart 
 of downtown Nashville\, Indiana. On display throughout its galleries is a
  prized collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sal
 e from regional award-winning member artists. The Guild also offers artis
 t demonstrations\, workshops\, and a variety of events and programs throu
 ghout the year.\n\nMarch – December: Monday–Saturday\, 11 – 5 and Sunday\
 , 12 – 4 or by appointment.\n\nWINTER HOURS: January – February: Thursday
  – Saturday 11 – 5 and Sunday 12-4 or by appointment.\n\nFor more informa
 tion\, please call the Guild at 812-988-6185 or visit our website: brownc
 ountyartguild.org/ https://browncountyartguild.org/
CATEGORIES:Gallery,Nashville,Visual-Arts
