SUMMARY: 2026 Patron & Young Artist Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:Annual Patron & Young Artist Exhibition 2026\n\nBrown County 
 Art Guild\n\nCall for Entries: January 9-11 & 16-18\, 2026\n\nExhibition 
 Dates: January 23– February 14\, 2026\n\nJudges: Guild Artists\, Mark Bur
 kett & Jeanne McLeish\n\nPrizes will be awarded in both divisions\n\nSubm
 issions:\n\nFramed and ready to hang 2-D work in any medium. Excludes fin
 e art photography\, digital & 3D.\n\nRequirements:\n\nArtwork cannot have
  been previously shown at the Guild. All artwork must remain on display a
 nd be available for sale for the entire show. A 40% Patron contribution t
 o the Guild for any work sold. Young Artists can sell their art consignme
 nt free or mark their work NFS. The Guild can refuse artwork to be consid
 ered inappropriate. A 2-5MB .jpeg file must accompany each entry and emai
 led to admin@bcartguild.org mailto:admin@bcartguild.org mailto:admin@bcar
 tguild.org - Image file must include name of artist\, title\, size\, med 
 & price. Please reference the “2026 Patron & Young Artist Exhibition” in 
 the subject line.\n\nDivisions:\n\nPatron - 19 years of age and older - e
 nter up to two submissions. $40 for the first submission\, includes one y
 ear membership. Discounted fee of $20 for optional second submission.\n\n
 Young Artist - 18 years of age and younger - free submission\, up to 2 fr
 amed pieces.\n\nGeneral Info:\n\nVisit our website for an application or 
 further information including eligibility\, details for painting sizes\, 
 entry fees & awards – browncountyartguild.org/event/the-patron-young-exhi
 bition/ https://browncountyartguild.org/event/the-patron-young-exhibition
 / https://browncountyartguild.org/event/the-patron-young-exhibition/\n\nD
 rop-off dates and times: January 9 -11 or 16-18\, 2026\n\nFriday & Saturd
 ay 11:00a – 5:00p or Sunday 12:00p – 4:00p\n\nAwards and artist reception
 : Saturday\, February 14\, 2026\, from 2:00p – 4:00p\, awards presented a
 t 3:00p\n\n**************************************************************
 ***********\n\nBrown County Art Guild – A not for profit organization loc
 ated in the heart of downtown Nashville\, Indiana. On display throughout 
 its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as cur
 rent works for sale from regional award-winning member artists. The Guild
  also offers artist demonstrations\, workshops\, and a variety of events 
 or programs throughout the year.\n\nMarch – December 2025\, Monday – Satu
 rday 11am-5pm & Sundays 12-4pm\n\nWinter Hours - January & February 2026\
 , Closed Monday-Wednesday or by appt. ~\n\nThursday-Saturday\, 11am-5pm ~
  Sunday\, 12-4pm
CATEGORIES:Exhibition,Gallery,Literary-Arts,Nashville
