SUMMARY: The Wind Rises (2013)
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the wondrous films of Hayao Miyazaki in a 4-film se
 ries at the Buskirk-Chumley Theater.\n\nThe Wind Rises is the 19th animat
 ed film written and directed by Hayao Miyazaki and produced by Studio Ghi
 bli. It is based on the serialized manga of the same name\, written and i
 llustrated by Miyazaki on Model Graphix magazine and Tatsuo Hori’s acclai
 med 1937 novel The Wind Has Risen.\n\nThe film chronicles the life of Jir
 o Horikoshi\, a Japanese aircraft designer who dreams of flight despite p
 oor eyesight. The story follows his journey as he designs planes\, naviga
 tes his love for a woman named Nahoko\, and grapples with the tragic impl
 ications of his work during the rise of World War II. It blends historica
 l events like the Great Kanto Earthquake with fictional elements\, offeri
 ng a mature and personal story about ambition\, love\, and the beauty and
  destruction of dreams\n\n2013\nRATED: PG-13\nLENGTH: 2H 6M\nFORMAT: DCP 
 (2D) english dub
