SUMMARY: Twin Peaks Season 2\, Episodes 10-13 | IU Cinema
DESCRIPTION:Laura's case now solved\, Twin Peaks experiences a strange di
 sappearance\, a surprising reappearance\, unexpected romances\, and one s
 eriously devilish little boy.\n\nEpisode 10 (“Dispute Between Brothers”):
  Sarah Palmer tries to accept all that has happened to her family. Dr. Ja
 coby returns from Hawaii. Cooper prepares to leave Twin Peaks. Mayor Milf
 ord objects to his brother's engagement to a younger woman.\n\nEpisode 11
  (“Masked Ball”): Mrs. Briggs talks about her husband's disappearance int
 o the woods. Nadine is put on the wrestling team\, where she falls for Mi
 ke Nelson. James is hired by the mysterious\, wealthy Evelyn Marsh. Dick 
 takes on an orphan\, Little Nicky.\n\nEpisode 12 (“The Black Widow”): Ben
  takes Bobby under his wing in a hope to destroy Hank and Jean. However\,
  Ben's mental state is starting to crack. Cooper starts to look at buying
  real estate. Major Briggs's supervisor reveals that Briggs was studying 
 the woods.\n\nEpisode 13 (“Checkmate”): Major Briggs has no memory of the
  place he was taken but now has an odd tattoo on his neck. Andy and Dick 
 break into Little Nicky's files. Evelyn asks James to kill her husband.\n
 \n[186 min total\; drama\, mystery\; English]
