SUMMARY: Night Club Dance Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Drawing on over 45 years of training\, teaching\, and competi
 ng\, Mary Hoedeman has created a clear\, approachable program designed to
  help dancers feel confident\, comfortable\, and successful on the social
  dance floor.\n\nNight Club is a sophisticated and elegant way to slow da
 nce — emphasizing balance\, connection\, musicality\, and ease rather tha
 n memorized patterns or performance.\n\nIn this workshop\, Mary breaks Ni
 ght Club down to its essentials\, identifying only the relevant steps and
  principles needed to accomplish the movement. From there\, dancers are g
 uided through a simple structure repeated 21 times — until the dance smil
 es back.\n\nThis method allows the body to learn naturally through repeti
 tion\, resulting in:\n\n  * Smooth\, relaxed movement\n  * Increased conf
 idence and balance\n  * Clear lead-and-follow connection\n  * A deeper se
 nse of musical timing\n\nThis workshop is appropriate for:\n\n  * New dan
 cers\n  * Experienced social dancers\n  * Anyone wanting a graceful\, con
 fident slow dance they can use immediately\n\nNo partner is required. Rol
 es rotate frequently\, and the environment is welcoming\, supportive\, an
 d grounded in real social dancing.\n\nThis is not about performance or pe
 rfection — it’s about learning to feel good while dancing.
CATEGORIES:
