SUMMARY: Wisdom of Happiness (2025)
DESCRIPTION:From Executive Producers Richard Gere and Oren Moverman.\nWIS
 DOM OF HAPPINESS shows us a timeless truth: happiness is still possible\,
  even in the midst of chaos and uncertainty.\n\nThis powerful message of 
 hope is delivered as a personal audience with one of the greatest living 
 thinkers\, Nobel Peace Prize winner\, Tenzin Gyatso\, known to billions a
 round the world as the Dalai Lama.\n\nSpeaking as a member of our single 
 global community\, he shares practical wisdom for finding peace\, compass
 ion\, and hope in the midst of chaos. With disarming clarity and deep hum
 anity\, he invites us to imagine—and help create—a world where compassion
  is activated as our strongest force for change\, and happiness is within
  reach for everyone.\n\nIn WISDOM OF HAPPINESS\, the Dalai Lama speaks di
 rectly to viewers\, sharing his Tibetan wisdom\, underscoring the oneness
  of humanity\, and offering a message of hope and serenity in troubled ti
 mes. He reflects on how each of us can overcome negative emotions and str
 engthen positive ones like love and compassion\, opening the path to happ
 ier\, more meaningful lives while contributing to a healthier and more ha
 rmonious future. He also emphasizes that the feminine principle of kindne
 ss and connection is urgently needed\, even suggesting the next Dalai Lam
 a may be female.\n\nThe film is a grand and immersive cinematic experienc
 e. The Dalai Lama guides us by asking how “modern” people can find peace 
 of mind despite the stresses of daily life\, the climate crisis\, and the
  anxieties of ongoing wars. That inner calm\, he reminds us\, enables us 
 to create peace and justice outwardly and to take action together.\n\nOne
  of the greatest living thinkers\, the 14th Dalai Lama is now 90 years ol
 d and looks back on a life that has\, perhaps unsurprisingly\, been the s
 ubject of various Hollywood film productions. Jetsun Jamphel Ngawang Lobs
 ang Yeshe Tenzin Gyatso\, the Dalai Lama’s full spiritual name\, is one o
 f the most well-known figures of our time. His tenure as the head of Tibe
 tan Buddhists has lasted longer than the reign of Queen Elizabeth II\, gi
 ven that he was enthroned at the age of five.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Film,In-Person,Tickets
