SUMMARY: From Deep w/ filmmaker | Cinematic Sports Documentary: History\,
  Politics\, Aesthetics
DESCRIPTION:Brett Kashmere’s 2014 film From Deep is an essay-style docume
 ntary that interrogates the game of basketball and its place in American 
 culture. Offering both critical sports history and experimental filmmakin
 g\, Kashmere blends archival footage\, mixtape aesthetics\, and social co
 mmentary to trace basketball’s evolution in U.S. culture\, specifically i
 n African American communities. This inventive blend of experimental form
  and social consciousness of sport marks a significant intervention in th
 e contemporary sport documentary landscape. [88 min\; documentary\, exper
 imental\; English]\n\nA Q&A with filmmaker Brett Kashmere will follow the
  screening.
