SUMMARY: 2026 Patron & Young Artist Exhibition Reception
DESCRIPTION:Patron & Young Artist Exhibition Reception\n\nFebruary 14\, 2
 026\n\n2-4pm\n\nAwards presented at 3pm\n\nThe Brown County Art Guild inv
 ites you to our upcoming Patron & Young Artist Exhibition Reception\, a c
 elebration of creativity and community spirit! Join us on Saturday\, Febr
 uary 14\, 2026\, from 2:00 PM to 4:00 PM at our gallery\, where you can i
 mmerse yourself in the beautiful works created by talented local artists.
 \n\nTake the opportunity to vote for the People's Choice Award\, allowing
  your voice to be heard in recognizing the remarkable talents of our arti
 sts. We are honored to have Guild Artist Members\, Mark Burkett & Jeanne 
 McLeish as the exhibition judges. The presentation of the awards begins a
 t 3:00 PM.\n\nThis event is free to the public\, and light refreshments w
 ill be served. We look forward to welcoming you to an afternoon filled wi
 th art\, community\, and celebration!\n\nThe Patron & Young Artist Exhibi
 tion is on display from January 23 - February 14\, 2026.\n\n-------------
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ---------------------------------\n\nBrown County Art Guild – A not for p
 rofit organization located in the heart of downtown Nashville\, Indiana. 
 On display throughout its galleries is a prized collection of historic pa
 intings as well as current works for sale from regional award-winning mem
 ber artists. The Guild also offers artist demonstrations\, workshops\, an
 d a variety of events or programs throughout the year.\n\nWinter Hours Ja
 nuary – February 2026: Closed Monday-Wednesday or by appt\, Open Thursday
 -Saturday 11am to 5pm\,\n\nSunday 12pm-4pm\n\nMarch – December 2026: Mond
 ay–Saturday\, 11 – 5 and Sunday\, 12 – 4\n\nFor more information\, please
  call the Guild at 812-988-6185 or visit our website: browncountyartguild
 .org/ https://browncountyartguild.org/
CATEGORIES:Exhibition,Free,Nashville,Visual-Arts
