SUMMARY: Punch-Drunk Love | Additional Films and Guests
DESCRIPTION:Punch-Drunk Love crawled so Uncut Gems could walk! Paul Thoma
 s Anderson's foray into a romantic (and still dark!) comedy is about as c
 haotic and off-kilter as one might expect. Barry Egan (Adam Sandler\, in 
 his first dramatic starring role) is a small business owner with seven si
 sters whose abuse has kept him alone and unable to fall in love. When a h
 armonium and a mysterious woman enters his life (Emily Watson)\, his roma
 ntic journey begins\, but not without an extortion side quest for the age
 s—enter Philip Seymour Hoffman in yet another small\, but wildly impactfu
 l\, role. Jon Brion (Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind\, Magnolia) he
 lps fuel the narrative with a baroque\, futurist score that helps Punch-D
 runk Love channel "the spirit of classic Hollywood musicals and the whims
 y of Jacques Tati into an idiosyncratic ode to the delirium of new romanc
 e" (Criterion Collection). [95 min\; drama\, comedy\, romance\; English]
CATEGORIES:
