SUMMARY: Guitar\, Boleros\, Y Amor
DESCRIPTION:Whether you are deeply in love or simply in love with the mus
 ic of love\, Bloomington Chamber\n\nSinger’s upcoming concert is perfect 
 for you. Join BCS as they present a program inspired by the\n\nmultifacet
 ed aspect of love. The concert\, entitled Guitar\, Boleros\, Y Amor will 
 be presented by the\n\nChamber Singers Sunday afternoon at 4:00 pm\, Febr
 uary 15th\n\n\, 2026\, at the Unitarian Universalist\n\nChurch of Bloomin
 gton located at 2120 N. Fee Lane\, Bloomington.\n\nConducted by artistic 
 director\, Caio Guimarães\, the Chamber Singers will be joined by Brazili
 an\n\nguitarist João Vitor as well as four-hand piano accompaniment provi
 ded by Edoardo Lenza and\n\nMatthew Gemmill. All are cordially invited to
  bask in the romance of the season as BCS leads you on\n\na romantic jour
 ney to Spain and Mexico. In-person tickets are available either through p
 re-sale or at\n\nthe door. General admission tickets are $20. Student tic
 kets will be available at the venue for $15\n\nwith student ID. A live-st
 ream option is also available. More information is available by visiting 
 the\n\nBloomington Chamber Singers’ website: http://www.chambersingers.in
 fo.\n\n
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Music,Live
