SUMMARY: Twin Peaks Season 2\, Episodes 14-17
DESCRIPTION:Things in Twin Peaks once again turn deadly as the truth abou
 t Cooper's shooting comes to light while his cat-and-mouse game with form
 er partner Windom Earle escalates.\n\nEpisode 14 (“Double Play”): Windom 
 Earle has taken his first victim in the deadly chess game. Audrey tells B
 obby they have to save Ben from his Civil War fantasy. Leo escapes.\n\nEp
 isode 15 (“Slaves and Masters”): The police look for James in the Marsh m
 urder. Bobby and Shelly tell Truman that Leo is gone and also reveal that
  Hank shot Leo the night the mill burned. Albert returns to Twin Peaks wi
 th information on Windom Earle.\n\nEpisode 16 (“The Condemned Woman”): Tr
 uman puts Hank in prison for the attempted murder of Leo\, while Hank poi
 nts the finger at Josie for the murder of Andrew Packard. Albert reveals 
 who shot Cooper. Ben enlists the help of John Justice Wheeler.\n\nEpisode
  17 (“Wounds and Scars”): Harry sinks into a deep depression after a trag
 edy. Norma's troubled sister\, Annie\, arrives in Twin Peaks. Wheeler and
  Audrey hit it off. Cooper's stalemate angers Earle.\n\n[185 min total\; 
 drama\, mystery\; English]
