SUMMARY: UP (2009) $5 movie night
DESCRIPTION:February 17th is National Random Acts of Kindness Day! Get ou
 t there with spontaneous acts of generosity\, compassion\, and goodwill f
 or others with the goal of spreading joy and positivity. And then bring y
 our loved ones and family to see this fantastically warm Pixar film\, “Up
 ” for $5 each.\n\nCarl Fredricksen\, a retired balloon salesman and widow
 er\, is part rascal\, part dreamer and ready for his last chance at high-
 flying excitement. Tying thousands of balloons to his house\, Carl sets o
 ff to South America and the lost world of his childhood dreams in order t
 o fulfill a promise that he made to his late wife. But unbeknownst to cur
 mudgeon Carl\, an overeager 8-year-old Wilderness Explorer who has never 
 ventured beyond his backyard is in the wrong place at the wrong time… Car
 l’s front porch.\n\nThe world’s most unlikely duo reach new heights and m
 eet fantastic friends like Dug\, a dog with a special collar that allows 
 him to speak\, and Kevin\, a rare 13-foot-tall flightless bird. Stuck tog
 ether in the wilds of the jungle\, Carl realizes that sometimes life’s bi
 ggest adventures aren’t the ones you set out to have.\n\nReviewers say “U
 p” is an emotional and imaginative film exploring love\, loss\, and adven
 ture\, and praise its poignant storytelling and opening sequence.\n\nRATE
 D: PG\nFORMAT: DCP\nLENGTH: 1hr 40min
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Film,In-Person,Tickets
