SUMMARY: The Waiting Game (2024) w/ filmmaker Q&A
DESCRIPTION:Q&A with Filmaker Michael Husain and former Pacers Darnell “D
 r. Dunk” HIllman and Dave Robisch after the film!\n\n\nAn incredible stor
 y of the ABA – a flamboyant rival league to the NBA – and its players. Th
 ey created much of what the billion dollar NBA is today–the 3-point shot\
 , slam dunk contest\, fashion and culture innovators–but then are forgott
 en in a business deal gone bad.\n\nThe Waiting Game is a powerful documen
 tary that reveals an incredible battle between the NBA and a tiny not-for
 -profit working to gain full recognition for the men of the ABA. It’s a f
 ight for benefits the players of the ABA felt were promised\, but never d
 elivered. While following an investigation of the legal trail of the ABA-
 NBA merger\, key impact journalism and the advocacy for justice\, the fil
 m reveals the lines that can stand between raw corporate interest and bas
 ic human dignity.\n\n“I’m an ABA guy. I got my start there. This is a ver
 y important film with a genuine hero at the center.” Bob Costas\n\n“This 
 is the REAL story of the guys I played with and the league that was so im
 portant to all of us. It made me cry and it made me proud. I want EVERYON
 E to see this.” “Dr Dunk” Darnell Hillman\, 3-time ABA Champion\, Winner 
 of first NBA Slam Dunk Contest\n\n“Here’s me explicitly asking you to ple
 ase watch Michael Husain’s documentary as soon as possible and recommend 
 it to your nearest NBA fanatic so that they can raise their voice for the
  legends associated with the ABA.” Pramit Chatterjee\, Rotten Tomato Revi
 ewer\n\nRATING: N/A\nLENGTH: 1hr 30min\nFORMAT: DCP
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Film,In-Person,Tickets
