SUMMARY: Filipino Culture Night
DESCRIPTION:Debut: Buhay at Unang Pag-Ibig (Life and First Love) is this 
 year’s Filipino Culture Night presented by the Filipino American Associat
 ion at IU\, celebrating 18 years of Filipino community at IU Bloomington.
  To honor this milestone\, the production brings a traditional Filipino d
 ebut to life on stage\, featuring the 18 Roses\, 18 Candles\, and 18 Trea
 sures.\n\nFollow Maia as she reconnects with her Filipino roots through d
 ance and finds herself caught between friendship and first love. With hig
 h energy cultural performances\, emotional storytelling\, and a blend of 
 contemporary and traditional music\, the show captures the excitement\, d
 rama\, and heart of growing up.\n\nWhether you are familiar with Filipino
  culture or experiencing it for the first time\, this one-night celebrati
 on offers a vibrant and heartfelt performance centered on love\, traditio
 n\, and community. First come\, first served light appetizers and refresh
 ments will be provided (while supplies last)\, proudly catered by Bloomin
 gton’s local Filipino restaurant\, Pinoy Garden Cafe. The dress code for 
 this event is semi-formal to align with the Debut theme. Dressing up is h
 ighly encouraged but not required.\n\nFor more information\, please visit
  the event website: filipinoculturenight2026.lovable.app/ https://filipin
 oculturenight2026.lovable.app/ https://filipinoculturenight2026.lovable.a
 pp/
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,In-Person,Live,Theatre
