SUMMARY: Bug | Transfixed: Michael Shannon on Screen\, Jorgensen Guest Fi
 lmmaker Series
DESCRIPTION:Michael Shannon and Ashley Judd give searing performances in 
 this skin-crawling exercise in fear and paranoia from director William Fr
 iedkin. Oklahoma waitress Aggie (Judd) lives a largely solitary life in a
  rundown motel. She's haunted by a tragic past and hounded by her ex-con 
 ex-husband (Harry Connick\, Jr.). When she sparks a romance with an eccen
 tric drifter\, Peter Evans (Shannon)\, she starts to feel hopeful again—u
 ntil Peter reveals he is a victim of government experimentation. The coup
 le begins to obsess over the nightmarish idea that they are infected by i
 nsects. Shannon reprises the role he originated in playwright Tracy Letts
 ' original London production of the same name. [102 min\; drama\, thrille
 r\, horror\; English]
CATEGORIES:Free
