SUMMARY: Saving Ava
DESCRIPTION:The biggest independent film to ever be made on IU’s campus. 
 A pulpy adventure inspired by the films of John Hughes and Rob Reiner\, s
 ix teenagers set out on a cross-country journey through the Midwest to fi
 nd their missing friend. As the miles pass\, old tensions from the turbul
 ent transition between high school and college resurface. Somewhere in be
 tween growing up and settling down\, a backdrop of summer crickets\, endl
 ess blue skies\, and open roads\, they confront their memories and misste
 ps that shaped their drifting friendships.\n\n\nThis film is family frien
 dly. (Includes depictions of alcohol consumption.)
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Film,In-Person,Tickets
